At 11:13 AM 5/7/2002, swh swh wrote:
>I need a solution to my problem of rust in the air intake vents.
>I've thought of sandblasting (carefully) but others have thougth this a 
>bad idea (messy, mostly).
>Someone also suggested putting a piece of sandpaper on a screwdriver and 
>attacking the problem that way.
>This method seems rather masochistic.
>Anyone have any ideas on how to get rid of that rust?

I vote for sandblasting.  I agree that the sandpaper/screwdriver method 
would be masochistic and on top of that, sandblasting will remove *all* of 
the rust while sandpaper will not (doesn't get into the minute crevices of 
rusted metal).

